exquisite /ɪkˈskwɪzɪt, ˈɛkskwɪzɪt/

1. ADJ Something that is exquisite is extremely beautiful or pleasant, especially in a delicate way. 精美的 

例： The Indians brought in exquisite beadwork to sell. 印地安人带了精美的珠饰来销售。 

2. exquisitely ADV 精美地 

例： ...exquisitely crafted dollshouses. …制作精美的玩具小屋。

